711005f-a.title: Manhattan: 9th Street (East) - University Place
711005f-a.text:
East 9th Street, north side, east from (No. 51) a point midway between
University Place and Broadway, and across the latter. The bridge affair
shown connects two buildings of John Wanamakers Department Store.

723680f-a.title: Manhattan: University Place - 9th Street
723680f-a.text:
University Place, west side, north from 9th Street. The b-story office
building, from 9th to 10th Streets, marked for sale, was built
prior to 1891, and will be demolished prior to 1930.
In the background may be seen the Metropolitan Life clock tower at
Madison Avenue and 24th Street.
May, 1913.
Brown Brothers.  Mieo 5 7S
